| 2 | Identify objects, classes and their relationships to design and construct moderatelycomplexobject-orientedsolution. | C | 2 |
| 3 | Apply and analyze the concept of encapsulation, method overloading, inheritanceandpolymorphism. | C | 3,4 |
| 4 | Create useful software applications using strong OOP concepts with effectivealgorithmicstrategies | C | 6 |

BT=Bloom’s Taxonomy, C=Cognitive domain, P=Psychomotor domain, A=Affective domain  

