| |  
|-|  
| This course covers the basics of digital logic circuits and design. Through the basic understanding of Boolean algebra and number systems it introduces the student to the fundamentals of combinational logic design and then to sequential circuits (both synchronous and asynchronous). Memory systems are also covered. Finally, the student is introduced to Register Transfer Logic design and the structured implementation of controllers and micro- programmed computers. | |
