## **CSC 1209 Islamic Studies / Humanities**  

|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Programme:** | CS/SE/AI | **Degree:** | BS | **Semester:** | 2 | **Credits:** | 2 |
| **Course Code:** | CSC 1209 | **Course:** | Islamic Studies | **Course Type:** | Core | | |
| **Course Area/Domain:** | GER | **Contact Hours:** | 2 hours/Week. | **Pre-Requisite:** | None | | |
| **Lab Course Name:** | Nil | **Lab Course Code:** | Nil | | | | |

  
|**Course Objectives** |  
|-|  
| To provide essential information about Islamic Faith. To improve skill of the students to perform prayers and other worships. To enhance understanding of the students regarding Islamic Civilization, jurisprudence, economic system and human rights. | |

* 
|**Course Description* |  
|-|  
| The course begins with explanation of Articles of Islamic Faith including some discussion on Quran and modern science. See rah of Prophet (PBUH) is discussed in length as well as his missions as given in the holy Quran. Selected verses of Holy Quran are discussed followed by basics of science of Hadith and 20 selected a ’hadith. Worships like Prayers, Zakat, Fasting and Hajj are covered next. Last lectures are devoted to Islamic civilization, jurisprudence, economic system and the human rights. | 

* 
|**Text/Reference Books :* |  
|-|  
| 1. Islamic Creed based on Quran and Sunnah / Author: Muhammad Bin Jameel Ar-Raheeq Al-<br>2. Makhtoom / Author: Saif-ur- Rahman al Mubarakpuri Introduction to Islam / Author: Muhammad<br>3. Hameed Ullah The Bible, the Quran and the Science / Author: Dr. Maurice Bucaille | |

