## **CSCL 2102 Lab Data Structures and Algorithms**  

|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Programme:** | CS/SE/AI | **Degree:** | BS | **Semester:** | 3 | **Credits:** | 1 |
| **Course Code:** | CSCL 2102 | **Course:** | Lab Data Structures and Algorithms | **Course Type:** | Core | | |
| **Course Area/Domain:** | Computer Science | **Contact Hours:** | 3 hours/Week. | **Pre-Requisite:** | CSC 1103, CSCL | | |
| **Lab Course Name:** | Data Structures and | **Lab Course Code:** | CSC 2102 | | | | |

  
|**Course Objectives** |  
|-|  
| The purpose of this course is to provide the students with solid foundations in the basic concepts of programming data structures and algorithms. The main objective of the course is to teach the students how to select, design, and implement data structures and algorithms that are appropriate for problems that they might encounter. This course is also about showing the correctness of algorithms and studying their computational complexities. This lab course is designed is designed to implement of core concepts of data structures and algorithms. | 

  
|**Course Description** |  
|-|  
| The main topics covered in this course are as follows Introduction, Arrays, Linked Lists, Stacks, Queues, analysis of algorithms, trees, binary search trees, hash tables, graphs, graph traversals, graph algorithms, Sorting. | |

* 
|**Text/Reference Books :* | 
|-|  
| 1. Data structures& Algorithms in C++, Michael T. Goodrich , Roberto Tamassis, and David Mount,<br>2. 2nd Edition, John Wiley ,2011 | |

