| **Week** | **Topics** 
|---|---|
| 1 | Introduction to MySQL -Installation and configuration |
| 2 | MYSQL tool description and detail |
| 3 | Create ER model using MySQL Data Modeling |
| 4 | Various Example of ER-Diagram with case study |
| 5 | Map ER model into relational Model |
| 6 | Practical view of relation, database schema -Different operations, transition, constraints on data |
| 7 | Create table -Insert , update and delete data -Basic retrieval queries using Select, from and where clause -Delete table and columns -Alter table |
| 8 | Use of JOIN in SQL and its types |
| 9 | Creation of table with attribute constraints -Key and referential integrity (Foreign key) constraints -Constraints on tuple using CHECK |
| 10 | Retrieving specific columns -Select distinct rows, Top rows, Like, IN, Between And operators -Logical operators -Ordering record |
| 11 | Generating sub queries -Aggregate functions -Group by and having clause |
| 12 | Introduction to front end tool -Understanding GUI |
| 13 | Connecting to database -Adding recording using hard coded SQL |
| 14 | Add, delete, and update a new record using forms -Record navigation using Forms - Reports and filters |
| 15 | Project Demo |

