| **Lab Course Name:** | Operating Systems | **Lab Course Code:** | CSC 2205 | | | | 
**Course Objectives**  
|
| |  
|-|  
| The purpose of this course is to conduct parallel lab sessions against the Theoretical Operating System classes. Whatever topics students are being taught in the Theory classes, some/most of those are supposed to be covered in these equivalent lab sessions in order to simulate those concepts programmatically and subsequently to provide a better understanding of the Theoretical course. | |
  
|**Course Description** |  
|-|  
|  | 
**Text|
/Reference Books :** 
| |  
|-| 
| 1. This is a lab course to operating system, its main aim is to introduce operating system functionality<br>2. to students. The lab course based on LINUX operating system. In lab students are given practical<br>3. overview of OS concepts.<br>4. Operating system concepts, Galvin, Peter B., Greg Gagne, and Abraham Silberschatz, null<br>5. Edition, John Wiley & Sons,2016 | |
**SYLLABUS**  
| **Week** | **Topics** |
|---|---|
| 1 | Operating systems overview, Introduction to Linux (Ubuntu Installation) |
| 2 | Introduction to Linux commands |
| 3 | How to write C program in Linux, Implementation the Process Management using fork |
| 4 | Implementation the Process Management using wait and exit |
| 5 | Inter process communication and implementation through pipes, Implementation of Threads |
| 6 | Execution of Multithreading Program, Implementation of Lock with and without busy- waiting |
| 7 | Implement the Producer & consumer Problem (Mutex-Semaphore) |
| 8 | Mid Term |
| 9 | Implement Deadlock creation and avoidance, Simulating Banker’s Algorithm for Deadlock Avoidance, Implement Process scheduling algorithm; FIFO, SJF, RR and PPS, Simulating multi-level queue scheduling algorithm. |
| 10 | Implement Deadlock Detection Algorithm in C |
| 11 | Implementation of Memory Management; allocation, resizing, releasing, clean |
| 12 | Simulation of Paging technique of Memory Management |
| 13 | Simulate page replacement algorithms : FIFO, LRU, LFU |
| 14 | Implementation of file organization techniques: single level, two-level and hierarchical level |
| 15 | Implementation of File Allocation concept using the technique indexed and link list, Implementation of Contiguous File Allocation using Compaction algorithm |

