## **CSC 4106 Parallel and Distributed Computing**  

|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Programme:** | CS/SE/AI | **Degree:** | BS | **Semester:** | 8 | **Credits:** | 3 |
| **Course Code:** | CSC 4106 | **Course:** | Parallel and Distributed Computing | **Course Type:** | Core | | |
| **Course Area/Domain:** | Computer Science | **Contact Hours:** | 3hours/Week. | **Pre-Requisite:** | CSC 3107, CSCL 3107 | | |
| **Lab Course Name:** | Nil | **Lab Course Code:** | Nil | | | | |

  
|**Course Objectives** |  
|-|  
| The objective of this course is to introduce the fundamentals of parallel and distributed processing, including system architecture, programming model, and performance analysis. It will focus on the basic architectural, programming, and algorithmic concepts in the design and implementation of parallel and distributed applications. | |

* 
|**Course Description* |  
|-|  
|  | |

* 
|**Text/Reference Books :* |  
|-| 
