| By the end of this course, students will be able to: 1. Demonstrate practical understanding of information security principles, standards, and policies. 2. Apply cryptographic techniques, authentication, and identity management in hands-on scenarios. 3. Analyze network threats and implement passive and active security measures. 4. Design, evaluate, and audit secure systems through real-world case studies. | |
  
|**Course Description** |  
|-|  
| The lab course provides hands-on experience in Information Security techniques, including cryptography, network security, threat analysis, authentication mechanisms, and auditing security systems. Students will implement concepts learned in theory, analyze security threats, and evaluate enterprise security measures through practical exercises. | |

