| 1 | Introduction to the Holy Quran – Revelation, structure, compilation, and importance in Islam. |
| 2 | Understanding the Quranic Language – Arabic basics, key terms, and interpretation (Tafsir) methods. |
| 3 | Themes and Structure of the Quran – Meccan vs. Medinan Surahs, thematic divisions, and chronology. |
| 4 | Fundamental Teachings I – Tawheed (Oneness of God) and Prophethood. |
| 5 | Fundamental Teachings II – Worship, prayer, and obedience to Allah. |
| 6 | Ethical Concepts – Honesty, integrity, justice, and social responsibility |
| 7 | Moral Principles – Compassion, patience, forgiveness, and humility. |
| 8 | Social Concepts – Family, community relations, equality, and charity. |
| 9 | Case Studies: Applying Quranic Ethics – Examples from contemporary social issues. |
| 10 | Decision Making Based on Quranic Guidance – Resolving personal and societal dilemmas. |
| 11 | Quranic Teachings and Personal Development – Self-discipline, accountability, and character building. |
| 12 | Responsibility and Leadership – Quranic principles in governance, work, and social roles. |
| 13 | Quranic Stories and Lessons – Prophets, moral parables, and life guidance. |
| 14 | Integrating Quranic Knowledge – Reflection exercises and practical applications. |
| 15 | Revision, Reflection, and Assessment – Summary, discussion, and presentations on applied learnings. |

**COURSE LEARNING OUTCOMES (CLOs)**  
| **CLO** | **Description** | **Domain** | **BT Level** |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Demonstrate anunderstandingofthe fundamental teachings ofthe HolyQuran. | C | 1 |
| 2 | Analyze ethical,moral,andsocial concepts from the Quran. | C | 2 |
| 3 | ApplyQuranic teachings toreal-worldethical andsocial issues. | C | 3 |
| 4 | Developa sense ofresponsibilitybasedonQuranic principles. | A | 3 |

BT=Bloom’s Taxonomy, C=Cognitive domain, P=Psychomotor domain, A=Affective domain  

